|Georgia]], 1954|nota=  [[1956 Melbourne Olympic Games]] swimmer. Former 50 meter freestyle [[World record]] holder and 200 meter freestyle relay [[World record]] holder.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[W.O. Payne]]|chapter= [[University of Georgia|Georgia]], 1900|nota=  [[Athletic Director]] at the [[University of Georgia]] 1936\u20131943.  [[Payne Hall (UGA)|Payne Hall]] on the [[University of Georgia|Georgia]] campus is named in his honor.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[United States Tennis Association|Gordon Smith]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[University of Georgia|Georgia]], 1975|nota=  Executive Director and COO of the [[United States Tennis Association]]. Member of the [[Intercollegiate Tennis Association|ITA]] Hall of Fame.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Tony Trabert]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[University of Cincinnati]], 1952|nota= [[Tennis]] champion, [[International Tennis Hall of Fame]] member|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Carl F. Ullrich]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[Cornell University]], 1950|nota= [[Athletic Director]] at [[West Point]] 1980\u20131990. Executive Director of the [[Patriot League]] 1989\u20131993.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Darrin Van Horn]]|chapter= [[University of Kentucky]], 1990|nota= Professional Boxer, 1989 [[IBF Junior Middleweight Champion]], 1991 [[IBF Super Middleweight Champion]]}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[O'Neill Williams]]|chapter= [[Emory University|Emory]], 1965|nota= Professional fisherman and outdoor personality. Host of TV's ''O'Neill Outside'' on [[Sun Sports]], [[SportSouth]] and the [[Versus (TV channel)|Versus]] channels.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Mason Bivins]]|chapter= [[University of North Georgia|UNG]], 2022|nota= Professional poker player and booler.|ref=}}\n}}\n\n==Politics and government==\nThose with careers spanning multiple categories are usually included with their highest or most prestigious office.\n\n===[[President of the United States]]===\n{{Mem/fstart\n|alist =\n{{Mem/f|name= [[President of the United States]] [[Grover Cleveland]] |chapter=Honorary br