 University|nota= Former Senior Vice-President of Programming at Clear Channel Radio (now iHeartMedia).|ref=https://sigmachi.org/home/alumni/significant-sigs/significant-sigs-list/|Graduation Date=1978}}<ref>https://sigmachi.org/home/alumni/significant-sigs/significant-sigs-list/</ref>\n\n===Other===\n\n{{Mem/fstart|alist=\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Andy Dunn]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter=[[Northwestern University|Northwestern]], 2000|nota=CEO of [[Bonobos (apparel)|Bonobos]].|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Harvey Hancock]]|chapter=[[University of Utah]], 1925|nota=Northern California [[Campaign manager]] for two successful races by [[Richard Nixon]]: 1950 United States Senate, and 1952 Presidential campaign, under [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]].|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Edward S. Rogers|Edward \"Ted\" Rogers]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter=[[University of Toronto]], 1956|nota=Former president and CEO of [[Rogers Communications]] Inc.|ref=}}\n}}\n\n==Business and technology==\n{{Mem/fstart|alist=\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Mike G. Hart]]|chapter=[[University of California, Davis]], 1985|nota=President and CEO of [[Sierra Energy]], President of [[Sierra Railroad]], named an \"Environmental Hero\" by the [[U.S. Environmental Protection Agency]], named a \"Champion of Change\" by the [[White House]].|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Roy Chapman Andrews]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter=[[Beloit College]], 1906|nota=Explorer, Adventurer and Naturalist who became the director of the American Museum of Natural History|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Philip Anschutz]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter=[[University of Kansas]], 1961|nota=Entrepreneur, [[Anschutz Entertainment Group]]|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=Jeff Arnold|chapter=[[University of Georgia|Georgia]], 1991|nota=Founder and former CEO of [[WebMD]]. Owner of [[HowStuffWorks]]|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Jim Barksdale]]|chapter=[[University of Mississippi|Mississippi]], 1965|nota=CEO of Netscape, 1995\u201399|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name=[[Reggie Bradford]]|chapter=[[University of Georgia|Georgia]], 1990|nota= Former [[chief market