0131939, [[Stanford University]], 1940\u20131941, [[University of Maryland]], 1942, 1946, [[University of Pittsburgh]], 1943\u20131945, [[National Football League|NFL]] [[Los Angeles Rams]] 1944\u20131949, [[University of Hawaii]] 1965;  [[College Football Hall of Fame]], 1968.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Phillippi Sparks]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[Arizona State]], 1991|nota= Defensive back [[New York Giants]] and  [[Dallas Cowboys]], [[National Football League]].|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Hank Stram]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[Purdue University|Purdue]], 1945|nota= Head [[coach (sports)|coach]], [[National Football League|NFL]] [[Kansas City Chiefs]], 1963\u20131974. [[Pro Football Hall of Fame]], 2003.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Fielding H. Yost]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[West Virginia University|West Virginia]], 1897|nota= Head [[Coach (sports)|coach]], [[University of Michigan]], 1901\u20131923, 1925\u20131926; [[College Football Hall of Fame]], 1951.|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[T. J. Yates]]|chapter= [[University of North Carolina]], 2011|nota= [[National Football League|NFL]] [[Quarterback]] for the [[Atlanta Falcons]].|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Ed White (American football)|Ed White]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[University of California, Berkeley]], 1969|nota= [[National Football League|NFL]] [[Minnesota Vikings]] (1969-1977), [[San Diego Chargers]] (1978-1985), Consensus [[All-American]] (1969),4x Pro Bowl (1975-77, 1979), [[College Football Hall of Fame]], University of California Hall of Fame, Pac-12  All Century Team, [[Breitbard Hall of Fame]], [[East-West Shrine Game | East-West Shrine Game Hall of Fame]], [[Minnesota Vikings|50 Greatest Minnesota Vikings]], [[San Diego Chargers Hall of Fame]].|ref=}}\n{{Mem/f|name= [[Harold Muller|Harold \"Brick\" Muller]]<sup>S</sup>|chapter= [[University of California, Berkeley]], 1922|nota= First player in Western United States to earn [[All-American]] honors (1921, 1922), [[Rose Bowl Game|Rose Bowl]] MVP (1921), Silver Medalist in High Jump a