ps://web.archive.org/web/20200228143440/https://www.ouest-france.fr/pays-de-la-loire/nantes-44000/coronavirus-la-patiente-prise-en-charge-au-chu-de-nantes-est-une-medecin-en-vacances-a-la-baule-8a524926-5a18-11ea-b880-542ae49135b4|archive-date=28 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Ain]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ledauphine.com/edition-genevois-chablais-bellegarde-pays-de-gex/2020/02/29/un-deuxieme-cas-de-coronavirus-dans-le-pays-de-gex|title=Ain. Un deuxi\u00e8me cas de coronavirus dans le Pays de Gex|website=ledauphine.com|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229113048/https://www.ledauphine.com/edition-genevois-chablais-bellegarde-pays-de-gex/2020/02/29/un-deuxieme-cas-de-coronavirus-dans-le-pays-de-gex|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Landes (department)|Landes]],<ref name=\"auto2\" /> [[Charente-Maritime]],<ref name=\":26\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lci.fr/sante/en-direct-coronavirus-trois-personnels-de-sante-de-l-hopital-tenon-contamines-2143314.html|title=EN DIRECT \u2013 Coronavirus : trois personnels de sant\u00e9 de l'h\u00f4pital Tenon contamin\u00e9s|website=LCI|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229112053/https://www.lci.fr/sante/en-direct-coronavirus-trois-personnels-de-sante-de-l-hopital-tenon-contamines-2143314.html|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Mayenne]],<ref name=\":25\" /><ref name=\":25\" /> [[Ille-et-Vilaine]],<ref name=\":29\">{{cite web|url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/info-ouest-france-coronavirus-un-premier-cas-detecte-rennes-une-femme-de-pompier-hospitalisee-6758739|title=INFO OUEST-FRANCE. Coronavirus : un premier cas d\u00e9tect\u00e9 \u00e0 Rennes, une femme de pompier hospitalis\u00e9e|last=GRISOT|first=Paul|date=29 February 2020|website=Ouest-France|language=fr|access-date=29 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200229172658/https://www.ouest-france.fr/sante/virus/coronavirus/info-ouest-france-coronavirus-un-premier-cas-detecte-rennes-une-femme-de-pompier-hospitalisee-6758739|archive-date=29 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Morbihan]],<ref name=\":35\" /> [[Haut-Rhin]],<ref name=\"auto4\" /> [[Eure]],<ref name=\"auto5\" /> [[Sarthe]],<ref name=\"auto3\" /> [[Gard]],<ref name=\":38\" /> [[Dr\u00f4me]],<ref name=\":39\" /> [[Sa\u00f4ne-et-Loire]],<ref name=\":40\" /> all the departments of the region [[Hauts-de-France]], except the [[Nord (French department)|Nord]],<ref name=\"20minutes2730587\">{{cite web|url=https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2730587-20200302-coronavirus-covid-19-desormais-present-toute-region-hauts-france|title=Le coronavirus est d\u00e9sormais pr\u00e9sent dans tous les Hauts-de-France|website=20 Minutes|language=fr|access-date=2 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302172701/https://www.20minutes.fr/sante/2730587-20200302-coronavirus-covid-19-desormais-present-toute-region-hauts-france|archive-date=2 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> and in the overseas territories of [[Saint Barth\u00e9lemy]] and [[Collectivity of Saint Martin|Saint Martin]].<ref name=\":33\" />\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/France medical cases}}\n\n== Simulation statistics ==\nSimulation studies helped convince the government that taking no action would result in large numbers of civilian casualties. In such a case between 30,000 and 100,000 more [[Intensive care unit|ICU]] beds would be required in the hospitals. In France there are 5,000 {{ill|reanimation service|fr|service de r\u00e9animation}} beds and 7,364 ICU beds. These simulations were provided by [[Neil Ferguson (epidemiologist)|Neil Ferguson]], epidemiologist at the [[Imperial College London]].<ref name=\"lemonde6033149\">[https://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2020/03/15/coronavirus-les-simulations-alarmantes-des-epidemiologistes-pour-la-france_6033149_3244.html Coronavirus : les simulations alarmantes des \u00e9pid\u00e9miologistes pour la France] 15 March 2020 ''Le Monde''. Retrieved 15 March 2020</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|COVID-19 pandemic in France}}\n* Data and maps, frequently updated:\n** {{cite web |url=https://coronavirus-global.com/france |title=Coronavirus France updates and news |trans-title=Latest news and statistics of coronavirus in France. |access-date=4 April 2020 |language=English, French, Spanish, Portuguese, German, Italian, Swedish, Norwegian, Finnish, Estonian, Russian}}\n\n{{2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic}}\n{{2020 coronavirus pandemic in France}}\n{{Portal bar|COVID-19|France|Medicine|Viruses}}\n\n{{#related:Emmanuel Macron}}\n{{#related:\u00c9douard Philippe}}\n{{#related:2019\u20132020 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in France| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by country and territory|France]]\n[[Category:January 2020 events in France]]\n[[Category:February 2020 events in France]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in France]]\n[[Category:Medical outbreaks in France]]\n", "name_user": "S17003", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(Fixed typo)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_France"}
{"title_page": "Dante Spinotti", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=February 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| image = \n| caption = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1943|8|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Tolmezzo]], [[Italy]]\n| occupation = Cinematographer\n| years_active = 1972-present\n}}\n'''Dante Spinotti''', [[A.S.C.]], A.I.C. (born August 22, 1943) is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[cinematographer]] and a member of the [[Board of Governors]] of the [[Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences]].<ref name=IMDb_Spinotti>{{cite web|title=Dante Spinotti|url=https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0005883/|publisher=IMDb|accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref> He is known for his collaborations with directors [[Michael Mann]], [[Michael Apted]], and [[Brett Ratner]], and is frequently credited with helping to pioneer the use of high-definition [[digital video]] in [[cinematography]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://britishcinematographer.co.uk/dante-spinotti-special-feature/|title=Dante Spinotti - British Cinematographer|date=2015-05-09|work=British Cinematographer|access-date=2018-03-18|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2016/artisans/festivals/dante-spinotti-technology-new-workflow-directors-personalities-1201922150/|title=Dante Spinotti on Technology, New Workflow, Directors\u2019 Personalities|last=Caranicas|first=Peter|date=2016-11-18|work=Variety|access-date=2018-03-18|language=en-US}}</ref> He is a [[BAFTA Award for Best Cinematography|BAFTA Award]] recipient and two-time [[Academy Award for Best Cinematography|Academy Award]] nominee (for [[L.A. Confidential (film)|''L.A. Confidential'']] and [[The Insider (film)|''The Insider'']]).\n\n==Biography==\nSpinotti was born in [[Tolmezzo]], near the [[Austria]]n border. He began experimenting with still photography at the age of 11 with a camera given to him by his uncle, a [[cinematographer]] and [[Film director|director]] specializing in documentaries and newsreels. He worked as a [[camera operator]] on documentaries for much of his early career.\n\nAmong the more notable films he has worked on are ''[[The Last of the Mohicans (1992 film)|The Last of the Mohicans]]'', ''[[Heat (1995 film)|Heat]]'', and ''[[L.A. Confidential (film)|L.A. Confidential]]''. Spinotti also was the cinematographer for [[Brett Ratner]]'s films, such as ''[[Red Dragon (2002 film)|Red Dragon]]'' (2002), ''[[After the Sunset]]'' (2004), and ''[[X-Men: The Last Stand]]'' (2006).\n\nSpinotti has the distinction of being the cinematographer on both film versions of author [[Thomas Harris]]' ''[[Red Dragon (novel)|Red Dragon]]'': [[Michael Mann (director)|Michael Mann]]'s [[Manhunter (film)|1986 adaptation]] (titled ''Manhunter''), and [[Brett Ratner]]'s [[Red Dragon (2002 film)|2002 adaptation]] (which retains the novel's original title). He won the Golden Camera 300 award at the [[Manaki Brothers Film Festival]] in [[Republic of Macedonia|Macedonia]] for lifetime achievement.\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Director\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n|1981\n|''[[La disubbidienza]]''\n|[[Aldo Lado]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1983\n|''[[Cinderella '80]]''\n|Roberto Malenotti\n|\n|-\n|''[[Dream of a Summer Night]]''\n|[[Gabriele Salvatores]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[Hearts and Armour]]''\n|[[Giacomo Battiato]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1984\n|''[[Basileus Quartet]]''\n|[[Fabio Carpi]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[Cos\u00ec parl\u00f2 Bellavista]]''\n|[[Luciano De Crescenzo]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1985\n|''[[The Berlin Affair]]''\n|[[Liliana Cavani]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[The Dark Side of Love]]''\n|[[Salvatore Samperi]]\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1986\n|''[[Crimes of the Heart (film)|Crimes of the Heart]]''\n|[[Bruce Beresford]]\n|\n|-\n|''[[Manhunter (film)|Manhunter]]''\n|[[Michael Mann]]\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[From the Hip (film)|From the Hip]]''\n|[[Bob Clark]]\n